constructor.details: Sets the deployer as the initial owner of the contract

deployLendingPool(address).custom:security: This function should only be called by the factory contract
deployLendingPool(address).details: This function creates a new LendingPool instance with the provided parameters. Only the factory contract should call this function to ensure proper pool management. Requirements: - Caller must be the factory contract - _router must be a valid router contract address

params._router: The address of the router contract that will manage the lending pool

returns._0: The address of the newly deployed LendingPool contract

setFactory(address).custom:security: Ensure the _factory address is a trusted contract before setting
setFactory(address).details: This function allows the owner to update the factory address. Once set, only the new factory address will be able to deploy lending pools. Requirements: - Caller must be the owner

params._factory: The address of the new factory contract

deployLendingPool(address).notice: Deploys a new LendingPool contract with specified parameters

factory().notice: The address of the factory contract that is authorized to deploy lending pools

owner().notice: The address of the contract owner who can set the factory address

setFactory(address).notice: Sets the factory address that is authorized to deploy lending pools
